              <h3>Explanation about html Tags</h3>
             <div class="all-explore">

              <h4>&rarr; What is the html Tags? Why we use it.</h4> 
               <div class="explore">
                 <p>Generally Tags are the starting and ending parts of an HTML element. They begin with &lt; symbol and end with &gt; symbol. Whatever written inside &lt; and &gt; are called tags.</p>
                 <p>I think HTML tags are almost like keywords where every single tag has unique meaning.</p>
                 <div id="ps-box" class="ps-box" style="margin: 2rem 0rem;">
                 <p>&lt;b&gt;    &lt;/b&gt;</p>
                 </div>
                 <p>Some tags don't have their corresponding closing tags and these are known as “Stand-Alone tags”, “Empty tags”, “Self-closing tags”. As given below;</p>
                 <div id="ps-box" class="ps-box" style="margin: 2rem 0rem;">
                 <p>&lt;input/&gt;</p>
                 </div>
                 <div id="ps-box" class="ps-box" style="margin: 2rem 0rem;">
                 <p>&lt;img/&gt;</p>
                 </div>
                 <div id="ps-box" class="ps-box" style="margin: 2rem 0rem;">
                 <p>&lt;hr/&gt;</p>
                 </div>
                 <div id="ps-box" class="ps-box" style="margin: 2rem 0rem;">
                  <p>&lt;br/&gt;</p>
                 </div>
                 <div id="ps-box" class="ps-box" style="margin: 2rem 0rem;">
                  <p>&lt;textarea/&gt;</p>
                 </div>
               </div>

               <h4>&rarr; What is the html Elements? Why we use it.</h4>
               <div class="explore">
                <p>As we know each html Elements enclose the contents in between the tags. They consist of some kind of structure or expression. It generally consists of a start tag &lt;h1&gt;, content like-(This is heading) and an end tag &lt;/h1&gt;.</p>
                <p>Whatever written within a HTML tag are HTML elements.</p>
                <div id="ps-box" class="ps-box" style="margin: 2rem 0rem;">
                <p>&lt;b&gt;This is the element because it consist some content as you can see inside tag&lt;/b&gt;</p>
                </div>
              </div>

              <h4>&rarr; Nested element?</h4>
                <div class="explore">
                  <p>HTML elements may contain other elements. This is called nesting, and to do it properly, the entire element (including its markup) must be within the start and end tags of the containing element (the parent). Proper nesting is one of the criteria of a well-formed document (a requirement for XHTML).</p>
                  <div id="ps-box" class="ps-box" style="margin: 2rem 0rem;">
                  <p>&lt;div&gt;&lt;h1&gt;This is the element because it consist some content as you can see inside tag&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</p>
                  </div>
                </div>

               <h4>&rarr; What is the html Attributes? Why we use it.</h4>
               <div class="explore">
                <p>HTML attributes are used to describe the characteristic of an HTML element in detail. It always placed in the opening tag &lt; of an element. It generally provides additional styling (attribute) to the element.</p>
                <p>HTML attributes specify various additional properties to the existing HTML element.</p>
                <div id="ps-box" class="ps-box" style="margin: 2rem 0rem;">
                <p>&lt;p align="center"&gt;This is paragraph.&lt;/p&gt;</p>
                </div>
              </div>

